#   SUBS-012: diff / object / history projectors do not cross submodule boundaries (LANDED)

**MEDIUM ‚Äî LANDED `7d37f90f` (2026-06-06).**  Reused SUBS-011's machinery in
two shapes (`beagle/BE.cli.c`): **whole-tree fan-out** (`diff:`/`tree:`/`refs:`
added to `be_projector_recurses` ‚Äî `diff:` aggregates each sub's path-prefixed
working-tree changes) and **path-in-mount routing** (`BEProjectorRouteToMount` +
`be_path_in_mount` ‚Äî a path-bearing projector whose path lands inside a mount is
rewritten mount-relative and relayed into the sub shard).  **Covered:** `diff:`
(aggregate), `tree:<gitlink>` (descends), `blob:<subpath>?ref`, `log:`/`blame:`
on a sub path.  **Deferred:** `refs:?**` sub-shard inclusion ‚Äî `refs:` itself
returns "projector not implemented" in keeper (pre-existing gap), so the
fan-out hook is wired but has nothing to fan into yet.  Repros `test/diff/06`,
`test/tree/01` added.  (Separate pre-existing parent-side bug found here:
`blob:<path>` without `?ref` ‚Üí KEEPNONE, filed as [SUBS-015].)

**MEDIUM (feature gap).**  Beyond search (SUBS-011), the remaining read-only
projectors are all parent-only at a gitlink boundary ‚Äî same root cause
(`BEProjector` never enumerates subs, and a sub path resolves only in the
parent shard, which holds a `160000` gitlink, not the sub's objects).

##  Observed (fixture: parent + `vendor/sub`)
 -  **`diff:`** ‚Äî a dirty *parent* file shows (`+// DIRTYPARENT` on `main.c`),
    but a dirty *sub* file (`vendor/sub/core.c`) never appears.  `be diff:`
    does not aggregate sub working-tree changes.
 -  **`tree:vendor/sub?master`** ‚Üí `PROJFAIL` (does not list the gitlink entry
    nor descend into the sub tree).
 -  **`blob:vendor/sub/core.c?master`** ‚Üí `KEEPNONE` (the path is a gitlink in
    the parent shard; blob resolution does not hop into the sub shard).
 -  **`refs:?**`** ‚Äî lists no sub refs (the sub shard's `?/<sub>/.<parent>/‚Ä¶`
    branches are invisible).
 -  **`log:` / `blame:`** ‚Äî operate on the parent history only; no per-sub or
    sub-path-aware view.

##  Expected
 -  `diff:` should aggregate each mounted sub's working-tree diff, path-
    prefixed (one merged hunk stream), like the verb reports already do.
 -  `tree:<gitlinkpath>` should either show the `160000` gitlink line or
    descend into the sub tree when the path points inside a mount.
 -  `blob:<subpath>?<ref>` and `log:`/`blame:` on a sub path should resolve in
    the sub shard.
 -  `refs:?**` (recursive) should optionally include sub shard refs.

##  Fix sketch
Same two-part shape as SUBS-011: (1) make `BEProjector` sub-aware ‚Äî for a path
that lands inside a mount, route to the sub shard; for whole-tree views
(`diff:`, `tree:`, `refs:`), enumerate mounts and relay/merge path-prefixed;
(2) honour `--nosub`.  Lower priority than SUBS-011 (search) but the same
machinery unlocks all of them.

##  Tests
Documented here; tests follow once the projector-recursion mechanism from
SUBS-011 lands (the `diff:` sub-change case is the natural first one).

